INSERT INTO `messages` (`id_mes`, `module_mes`, `language_mes`, `message_mes`) VALUES(1703, 'standard', 'en', '<div class="rowComment">\r\n<h1>Working tags:</h1>\r\n<div class="retrait">\r\n<h3>Display the content of the tag if the condition is met:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code"> &lt;atm-if what="<span class="keyword">condition</span>"&gt; ... &lt;/atm-if&gt; </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">condition</span> : Condition to meet to display the content of the tag. Common use is to validate the presence of a non negative value. This condition may also take all the valid forms of a PHP condition (see: <a target="_blank" class="admin" href="http://www.php.net/if">The structures of a PHP&#160;control</a>). The condition will be met if the value exists or if it is not negative or if it is not equal to false.</li>\r\n    <li>An attribute <span class="keyword">name </span>(optional) can be added if you want to run the opposite condition (else) using a tag <span class="keyword">atm-else</span> (see below). This attribute can contain only alphanumeric characters (a-zA-Z0-9_. -).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class="code">&lt;atm-else for="<span class="keyword">if-name</span>"&gt;  ... &lt;/atm-else&gt; </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">for </span>: name of the atm-if tag of reference. The content of this tag will be displayed only if the condition of the tag atm-if of reference is not met.</li>\r\n    <li>An attribute <span class="keyword">what </span>(optional) may be added if you want to add an additional condition to display the content of this tag. Common usage is to validate the presence of a nonzero value.&#160; This condition may also take all the valid forms of a PHP condition  (see: <a target="_blank" class="admin" href="http://www.php.net/if">The structures of a  PHP&#160;control</a>). The condition will be met if the value exists or if it  is not negative or if it is not equal to false.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Assign a value to a variable:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code">&lt;atm-setvar vartype="<span class="keyword">type</span>" varname="<span class="keyword">name</span>" value="<span class="keyword">varValue</span>" /&gt; </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">type </span>: Type of the variable to assign: <span class="vertclair">request</span>, <span class="vertclair">session</span> or <span class="vertclair">var</span>.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">name </span>: Name of the variable to assign. Attention, reassigning an existing variable will delete the former value.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">varValue</span> : Value to assign to the variable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Create an opening or a closing XHTML tag</h3>\r\n<p>In some cases, it may be interesting to create an opening or closing XHTML tag inside another tag (eg an atm-if tag). But this scenario breaks the XML syntax. In this case, you can use both tags:</p>\r\n<p><span class="code">&lt;atm-start-tag  tag="<span class="keyword">tagName</span>" /&gt; </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">tag </span>: Name of the opening tag to display.</li>\r\n    <li>You can then add as many attributes you want, they will all be added to the generated tag.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class="code">&lt;atm-end-tag  tag="<span class="keyword">tagName</span>"  /&gt; </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">tag </span>: Name of the closing tag to display.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Exemple :</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nYour row contains the following code:<br />\r\n<span class="code">&lt;atm-if what="condition1"&gt;<br />\r\n&#160;&#160;&#160; &lt;atm-start-tag tag="div" class="class1" /&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;/atm-if&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;atm-if what="condition2"&gt;<br />\r\n&#160;&#160;&#160;  &lt;atm-start-tag tag="div" class="class2" /&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;/atm-if&gt;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n... some XHTML content ...<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&lt;atm-tag-end tag="div" /&gt;<br />\r\n</span></p>\r\nIf condition 1 is fulfilled, you will get the following code:<br />\r\n<span class="code"> &lt;div class="class1"&gt;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n... some  XHTML content ...<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&lt;/div&gt;<br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div class="retrait">\r\n<h3>Reload a zone in AJAX:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code">&lt;atm-xml what="<span class="keyword">condition</span>"&gt; ... &lt;/atm-xml&gt; </span><br />\r\nAllows to reload a specific zone in the page via an AJAX request.<br />\r\nIf the HTTP request calling the current page contains the parameters verifying the attribute <span class="keyword">condition</span>, then only the content of the tag atm-xml will be sent back in response to the HTTP request. The rest of the content of the current page will be ignored.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor further information, consult the <a target="_blank" href="http://man.automne-cms.org">Automne manual on line</a> or study the Polymod modules within the Automne demo that use this function.\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">condition</span> : Condition to meet to obtain the content of the tag atm-xml.</li>\r\n    <li>A <span class="keyword">strict </span>attribute (optional) can be used to remove the tag &lt;[CDATA[ ... ]]&gt; around the results returned in the tag <span class="vertclair">data </span>of the AJAX response, thus providing valid XML that can then be parsed by Javascript. <br />\r\n    This attribute accepts a boolean value (<span class="vertclair">true </span>to remove the cdata or&#160;<span class="vertclair">false </span>to keep it).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Example with the help of JQuery :</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nYour row has the following code:<br />\r\n<span class="code">&lt;atm-xml what="<span class="keyword">{request:string:out} == ''xml''</span>"&gt;<br />\r\n&#160;&#160;&#160; ... search news ...<br />\r\n&lt;/atm-xml&gt;</span><br />\r\nIf you use the following AJAX request toward the page containing this row:<br />\r\n<span class="code"> $.ajax({<br />\r\n&#160;&#160;&#160;type:&#160;"POST",<br />\r\n&#160;&#160;&#160;url:&#160;pageURL,<br />\r\n&#160;&#160;&#160;data:&#160;''<span class="keyword">out=xml</span>&amp;cat='' + $(''#cat'').val(),<br />\r\n&#160;&#160;&#160;success:&#160;displaySearch<br />\r\n}); </span><br />\r\nThen the news search will be reloaded with the parameter of the selected category and only the content of this zone will be returned:<br />\r\n<span class="code"> &lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;response xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"&gt;<br />\r\n&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;error&gt;0&lt;/error&gt;<br />\r\n&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;data&gt;&lt;![CDATA[<span class="keyword"> ... the content of the atm-xml tag corresponding to the new search launched ... </span>]]&gt;&lt;/data&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;/response&gt; </span></div>\r\n<h3>Title of the current page:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code">&lt;atm-title /&gt;</span></div>\r\n<h3>Values of the current page :</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait">\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code">&lt;atm-page name="<span class="keyword">dataName</span>" /&gt;</span></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">dataName :</span>&#160;Name of the value to display from the current page. The following values are accepted:<br type="_moz" />\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">id </span>: identifier of the current page.</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">url </span>: address of the current page.</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">title </span>: title of the current page (equivalent of the tag &lt;atm-title /&gt;).</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">linktitle </span>: link title of the current page.</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">codename </span>: codename of the current page (if exists).</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">keywords</span>, <span class="vertclair">description</span>, <span class="vertclair">category</span>, <span class="vertclair">author</span>, <span class="vertclair">replyto</span>, <span class="vertclair">copyright</span>, <span class="vertclair">language</span>, <span class="vertclair">robots</span>, <span class="vertclair">pragma</span>, <span class="vertclair">refresh</span>, <span class="vertclair">metas </span>: meta-datas of the current page.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Values of the current website :</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait">\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code">&lt;atm-website name="<span class="keyword">dataName</span>" /&gt;</span></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">dataName :</span>&#160;Name of the value to display from the current website. The following values are accepted:<br type="_moz" />\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">root </span>: identifier of the root page of the current website.</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">domain&#160;</span>: domain name of the current website.</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">title </span>: title of the current website.</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">codename </span>: codename of the current website.</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">keywords</span>, <span class="vertclair">description</span>, <span class="vertclair">category</span>, <span class="vertclair">author</span>, <span class="vertclair">replyto</span>, <span class="vertclair">copyright</span>, <span class="vertclair">language</span>, <span class="vertclair">robots</span>, <span class="vertclair">favicon</span>,&#160;<span class="vertclair">metas </span>: meta-datas of the current website.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Page redirection:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code">&lt;atm-redirect url="<span class="keyword">urlValue</span>" /&gt;</span>\r\n<p>This code allows you to redirect the current page to another page or to another site.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">urlValue :</span>&#160;URL of the page to redirect the current page.</li>\r\n    <li>This tag accepts an optional parameter <span class="keyword">type </span>to specify the type of redirection by default: <span class="vertclair">301 </span>or <span class="vertclair">302 </span>(default).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Header code :</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code">&lt;atm-header&gt; ... &lt;/atm-header&gt;</span>\r\n<p>This tag allows you to execute code before processing the current page. It allows you to declare variables or to do actions before anything else on the page.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Display in the administration:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait">\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code">&lt;atm-admin&gt; ...   &lt;/atm-admin&gt;<br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<p>The content of this tag will be visible only if you are in the  administration of Automne.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="retrait">\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code">&lt;atm-noadmin&gt; ...    &lt;/atm-noadmin&gt;<br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<p>The content of this tag will not be visible if you are in the  administration of Automne.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Display in the page edition:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait">\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code">&lt;atm-edit&gt; ...   &lt;/atm-edit&gt;<br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<p>The content of this tag will be visible only if you are currently  editing the page in the administration of Automne.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="retrait">\r\n<div class="retrait"><span class="code">&lt;atm-noedit&gt; ...    &lt;/atm-noedit&gt;<br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<p>The content of this tag will not be visible if you are currently  editing the page in the administration of Automne.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&#160;</p>');
INSERT INTO `messages` (`id_mes`, `module_mes`, `language_mes`, `message_mes`) VALUES(1704, 'standard', 'en', 'Working tags');
INSERT INTO `messages` (`id_mes`, `module_mes`, `language_mes`, `message_mes`) VALUES(1705, 'standard', 'en', '<div class="rowComment">\r\n<h1>General variables:</h1>\r\n<div class="retrait">\r\n<h3>Variables relative to pages:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait">Variables relative to pages are of the form <span class="vertclair">{page:<span class="keyword">ref</span>:<span class="keyword">type</span>}</span>:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">ref </span>: <em><strong>Identifier</strong></em> or <em><strong>codename </strong></em>of the page to which it is referenced, can be a numerical ID&#160;of a page or an alphanumerical codename, ''<span class="vertclair">self</span>'' to refer to the current page or ''<span class="vertclair">father</span>'' to refer to the direct parent page.<br />\r\n    <strong>Attention </strong>designate a page with a codename,<span class="vertclair"> self</span> or by <span class="vertclair">father&#160;</span>makes sense only if you are in a page (ie in a page template or row). In a RSS feed or in a WYSIWYG plugin, the page makes no sense, then you can not use the codename, <span class="vertclair">self </span>or <span class="vertclair">father&#160;</span>to&#160;designate one page, in this case you must use an identifier.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">type</span> : type of date wanted for the page among the following:\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">url</span> :&#160;address of the page,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">id</span> :&#160;identifier of the page,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">title</span> :&#160;name of the page,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">exists </span>: does the page exists and is it public?</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">link</span>, <span class="vertclair">linktitle </span>: link title of the page page,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">website </span>: page website identifier,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">codename </span>: codename of the page if it exists,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">language </span>: page language,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">printurl</span> :&#160;print page address,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">keywords</span>, <span class="vertclair">description</span>, <span class="vertclair">category</span>, <span class="vertclair">author</span>, <span class="vertclair">replyto</span>, <span class="vertclair">copyright</span>, <span class="vertclair">robots</span>, <span class="vertclair">pragma</span>, <span class="vertclair">refresh</span>, <span class="vertclair">metas </span>: Metas datas of the page.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Relative variables to data sent (via an address or a form):</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait">These variables correspond to a variable coming from the submission of a form or from a parameter of a link having been brought to the current page. <br />\r\nThey are of the form <span class="vertclair">{request:<span class="keyword">type</span>:<span class="keyword">name</span>}</span> :\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">type</span> : Corresponds to the type of variable expected, among the following: <br />\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">int </span>: whole number,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">string </span>: chain of characters,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">safestring </span>: chain of characters without HTML code,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">bool </span>: boolean,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">array</span>: table of values,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">email </span>: valid email,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">date </span>: valid date without time (returns the date in the MySQL format: YYYY-MM-DD),</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">datetime </span>: valide date with time (returns the date in the MySQL format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS),</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">localisedDate</span> : valid date without time (returns the date in the format of your chosen language: %s).</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">name</span> : Corresponds to the name of the variable wanted (name of the parameter in the URL or the name of the form field).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Session variables:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait">These variables are available throughout the duration of the visit to the site. <br />\r\nThey have the following form <span class="vertclair">{session:<span class="keyword">type</span>:<span class="keyword">name</span>}</span>:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">type</span> : Corresponds to the type of variable expected, among the following:\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">int </span>: whole number,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">string </span>: chain of characters,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">bool </span>: boolean,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">array</span>: table of values,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">email </span>: valid email,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">date </span>: valid date without time (returns the date in the MySQL format: YYYY-MM-DD),</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">datetime </span>: valide date with time (returns the date in the MySQL format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS),</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">localisedDate</span> : valid date without time (returns the date in the format of your chosen language: %s).</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">name</span> : Corresponds to the name of the variable wanted (name of the session variable).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Variables:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait">These variables correspond to the classic PHP variables. <br />\r\nThey have the following form <span class="vertclair">{var:<span class="keyword">type</span>:<span class="keyword">name</span>}</span>:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">type</span> : Corresponds to the type of variable expected, among the following:\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">int </span>: whole number,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">string </span>: chain of characters,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">bool </span>: boolean,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">array</span>: table of values,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">email </span>: valid email,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">date </span>: valid date without time (returns the date in the MySQL format: YYYY-MM-DD),</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">datetime </span>: valide date with time (returns the date in the MySQL format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS),</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">localisedDate</span> : valid date without time (returns the date in the format of your chosen language: %s).</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">name</span> : Corresponds to the name of the variable wanted (name of the PHP variable).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Constants:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait">These variables correspond to the classic PHP constants. <br />\r\nThey have the following form <span class="vertclair">{constant:<span class="keyword">type</span>:<span class="keyword">name</span>}</span>:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">type</span> : Corresponds to the type of constant expected, among the following:\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">int </span>: whole number,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">string </span>: chain of characters,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">bool </span>: boolean,&#160;</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">email </span>: valid email,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">date </span>: valid date without time (returns the date in the MySQL format: YYYY-MM-DD),</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">datetime </span>: valide date with time (returns the date in the MySQL format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS),</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">localisedDate</span> : valid date without time (returns the date in the format of your chosen language).</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">name</span> : Corresponds to the name of the constant wanted (name of the PHP constant).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Server variables:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait">These variables correspond to the <a target="_blank" href="http://php.net/manual/en/reserved.variables.server.php">$_SERVER</a> PHP variables. <br />\r\nThey have the following form <span class="vertclair">{server:<span class="keyword">type</span>:<span class="keyword">name</span>}</span>:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">type</span> : Corresponds to the type of variable expected. In the case of server variables, they are usually of type <span class="vertclair">string</span>.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">name</span> : Corresponds to the name of the variable (name of the serveur variable expected).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Variables relative to users:</h3>\r\n<div class="retrait">These relative variables to users have the following form <span class="vertclair">{user:<span class="keyword">id</span>:<span class="keyword">type</span>}</span>:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">id </span>: Identifier of the user to which it is refered, can be a numerical ID of a user or ''<span class="vertclair">self</span>'' to refer to a current user (only if the verification of the client-side rights are active in the Automne parameters).</li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">type</span> : Corresponds to the type of variable expected, among the following: <br />\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">id </span>: user numeric identifier,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">login </span>: user identifier,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">fistName </span>: first name,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">lastName </span>: last name,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">fullName </span>: first and last name,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">email</span>: email,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">language </span>: returns a CMS_language object corresponding to the language of the user account,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">active </span>: boolean, <span class="vertclair">true</span> for active, <span class="vertclair">false</span> for inactive,</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">deleted </span>: boolean, <span class="vertclair">true</span> for deleted, <span class="vertclair">false</span> for existing.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1>Variables treatment - Helpers :</h1>\r\n<div class="retrait">To restate the above variables and the variables of the elements of Polymod modules, you have at your disposal a set of helpers capable of transforming the content of these variables. You can truncate them, changing its case, cleaning the content (remove the HTML for example), etc..</div>\r\n<div class="retrait">&#160;</div>\r\n<div class="retrait">The format of this helpers is&#160;<span class="vertclair">{helper:<span class="keyword">function</span>:<span class="keyword">content</span>}</span>:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">function</span>: <a target="_blank" href="http://www.php.net/manual/ref.strings.php">PHP function</a> to use to transform the contents of your variable. This is the function name to be used, for example:<br />\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.php.net/manual/function.substr.php">substr</a>: Returns a string segment.</li>\r\n        <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.php.net/manual/function.strtoupper.php">strtoupper</a>: Returns a string to uppercase.</li>\r\n        <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.php.net/manual/function.strtolower.php">strtolower</a>: Returns a string to lowercase.</li>\r\n        <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.php.net/manual/function.htmlspecialchars.php">htmlspecialchars</a>: Convert special characters to HTML entities.</li>\r\n        <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.php.net/manual/function.urlencode.php">urlencode</a>: Encode a string to URL.</li>\r\n        <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.php.net/manual/function.strip-tags.php">strip_tags</a>: Removes HTML and PHP tags from a string.</li>\r\n        <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.php.net/manual/function.strpos.php">strpos</a>: Find position of a character in a string.</li>\r\n        <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.php.net/manual/function.str-replace.php">str_replace</a>: Replaces all occurrences in a string.</li>\r\n        <li>...</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    In addition to traditional PHP functions, you can use any PHP function or class static method <a target="_blank" href="http://www.automne-cms.org/api/">defined in Automne</a> or that you have defined yourself in your own PHP code. For example:<br />\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.automne-cms.org/api/Automne/common/SensitiveIO.html#ellipsis">io::ellipsis</a>: Truncate a string and adds an ellipse.</li>\r\n        <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.automne-cms.org/api/Automne/common/SensitiveIO.html#isPositiveInteger">io::isPositiveInteger</a>: Check if a number is a positive integer.</li>\r\n        <li>...</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    If an error occurs while processing the requested function (the function does not exist or is not correct usage), the helper will return the original value without changing it. See the Automne error log for more information on the nature of the error.<br />\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword" style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(187, 17, 17); ">content</span>: Content to change by the helper. This can be fixed string or content of a variable. Examples:\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">{helper:strtoupper:</span><strong>abc</strong><span class="vertclair">}</span>: Pass the string "abc" to uppercase.</li>\r\n        <li><span class="vertclair">{helper:strtoupper:</span><strong>{request:string:text}</strong><span class="vertclair">}</span>: Pass in upper case the contents of the variable {request:string:text}.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Parameters:</h3>\r\n<p>A number of features require passing parameters to function. Example, the substr function requires two parameters to split a string: one to determine the cut start and another to determine the length of the cut. <br />\r\nYou can specify as many parameters as you wish. Separate each of them with characters "pipes": | .</p>\r\n<p>Examples:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="vertclair">{helper:substr:</span><strong>abcdef|1|3</strong><span class="vertclair">}</span>: Cut the string "abcdef" from the first character and retains three characters long.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="vertclair">{helper:strtoupper:</span><strong>{request:string:text}|0|{var:int:length}</strong><span class="vertclair">}</span>: Cuts the contents of the variable {request:string:text} to {var:int:length} of length.&#160;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Nesting helpers:</h3>\r\n<p>It is quite possible to nest helpers into each other to achieve a processing chain.</p>\r\n<p>Examples:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">{helper:ucfirst:</span><span class="vertclair">{helper:strtolower:</span><strong>{var:string:text}</strong><span class="vertclair">}</span><span class="keyword">}</span>: Change the contents of the variable {var:string:text} in lower case then capitalize the first letter of the resulting content.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">{helper:io::ellipsis:</span><span class="vertclair">{helper:strip_tags:</span><strong>{var:string:text}</strong><span class="vertclair">}</span><span class="keyword">|10}</span>: Removes HTML tags from the contents of the variable {var:string:text} then make an ellipse to 10 characters in the resulting content.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>');
